President Joe Biden has appointed William M. Russo as the Assistant Secretary of State for Global Public Affairs at the U.S. Department of State. Russo is currently the Acting Principal Deputy Assistant Secretary of State in the Bureau of Global Public Affairs. He previously served as the Bureau's Deputy Assistant Secretary for Strategic Messaging and as Advisor to then-Deputy Secretary Antony Blinken. Russo has also worked as the Deputy Communications Director for Press on the Biden-Harris campaign and as the Spokesperson for President Biden during his vice presidency in the Obama-Biden Administration. He began his government service in the Office of then-Vice President Joe Biden and has held various roles, including Senior Advisor to then-National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan. Russo holds an M.A. in Environment, Development, and Policy from the University of Sussex and an Honors B.A. in Political Science, History, and English from the University of Delaware.